I"Ý<p align="justify">I am one of the co-founders of  <a href="https://luahealth.io/" target="_blank">Lua Health</a>, a pioneering startup dedicated to enhancing mental well-being in the corporate realm. Lua Health specializes in discreetly and precisely identifying workplace-related wellness issues, offering a clear path towards early intervention. We firmly believe that the future of well-being lies in prevention and early detection, ensuring individuals receive the assistance they need when it matters most. Through our innovative SaaS-based solution, we empower businesses to provide timely and tailored support to their employees. As a spinoff from the University of Galway, our technology is rooted in decades of research in psycholinguistics.</p>

<p align="justify">I hold the role of a research fellow at the <a href="https://dsi.universityofgalway.ie/" target="_blank">Data Science Institute (DSI)</a>, which is part of the <a href="http://www.universityofgalway.ie/" target="_blank">University of Galway</a>. Within the institute, I am an active member of the <a href="https://www.universityofgalway.ie/dsi/nlp_unit/" target="_blank">Unit for Natural Language Processing (UNLP)</a>, led by <a href="https://www.universityofgalway.ie/our-research/people/engineering-and-informatics/paulbuitelaar/" target="_blank">Paul Buitelaar</a>. My primary research centres on the integration of terminology and knowledge graphs into neural machine translation architectures. Additionally, I've been working on dialogue systems and natural language generation, particularly in the context of multi-modal data. My research is supported by the <a href="https://www.insight-centre.org/" target="_blank">Insight SFI Research Centre for Data Analytics</a>, a nationwide institute that is also hosted within DSI. </p>
